OL,4,CVictoria Cross: 'Inspiring' WW1
OL,5,Cmessenger's medal sold for #248,000
OL,6, A Victoria Cross awarded to a World War
OL,7, One soldier who braved enemy fire to
OL,8, deliver orders to a stranded platoon
OL,9, has sold for #248,000 at auction.
OL,11,FPte James Towers received the medal for
OL,12,Fvolunteering to take the orders despite
OL,13,Fhaving seen five messengers shot down
OL,14,Fin Mericourt, France in October 1918.
OL,16,FMore than a decade later, the Broughton
OL,17,Ffarmer told a newspaper he felt he had
OL,18,Fto help, as "they were my pals".
OL,20,FThe medal previously sold for #144,000
OL,21,Fin an auction in 2015.
